  "title": "🎤Karaoke Receptionist cum Cashier | Bugis |Gross Up to 3,000",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description & Requirements</strong></p><h3>🕒 <strong>Working Hours</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Night Shift:</strong> 6:30 PM to 3:30 AM</li><li><strong>5 to 6 working days per week (schedule to be discussed)</strong></li></ul><h3>🛎️ <strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Front Desk Reception</strong>Welcome and check-in guests.<br />Introduce room types, rates, and promotions.<br />Guide guests to their rooms.</li><li><strong>Cashiering Duties</strong>Process payments for rooms, food & beverages.<br />Handle cash, NETS, and credit card transactions.<br />Issue receipts and ensure billing accuracy.</li><li><strong>Daily Cash Reconciliation</strong>Ensure cash balance matches system records.<br />Handle refunds, vouchers, and discounts as needed.</li><li><strong>Customer Service</strong>Respond to phone and walk-in enquiries.<br />Manage guest feedback and escalate when necessary.</li><li><strong>Administrative & Housekeeping Support</strong>Keep front desk area clean and organized.<br />Assist in ensuring rooms are in good condition for guests.</li><li><strong>Team Collaboration</strong>Coordinate with service and cleaning teams for smooth operations.</li></ul><h3>✅ <strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li>Secondary school education or higher.</li><li>Experience in cashiering, front desk, or customer service is preferred.</li><li>Able to communicate in English and Mandarin.</li><li>Comfortable handling cash and POS systems.</li><li>Responsible and service-oriented.</li><li>Able to commit to night shifts and weekend work.</li><li></li></ul><p>EA Personnel Name: Nicholas Wong</p><p>EA Personnel No: R23113643</p><p>EA License No: 23C1703</p>",
